        <h2>Why are Kirby Fans Privilaged?</h2>
        <img src="Kirbo_Stare.png" width=100 alt="Kirby is supposed to be here :[">
        
        <h3>They've never suffered a day in their lives</h3>
        <p>Kirby fans don't know what it's like to have your favorite series release a game and have it absolutely bomb, or see everything go off the rails for a long period of time, potentially never recovering. All mainline kirby games are consistently solid, with not a single dud in the catalog. Some games are more memorable than others, but they all have their merit.</p>
       
        <h3>They get new games consistently</h3>
        <p>Kirby games come out on a very consistent basis. Besides the Gamecube era, where they only had kirby air ride on the system since a game got canceled, Kirby fans always get something good. There's rarely been an entire year without at least a large side game releasing. Not only are these games of high quality, but kirby fans never have to go long without something new.</p>

        <h3>The fact Kirby Air Riders exists</h3>
        <p>They really got a sequal of a spin-off made on a system that didn't do the best just because it was held dear by the people who ended up playing it. It's a game made pretty much for its fans, which I think is really cool considering how detached nintendo can be sometimes.</p>

